observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the:

a.	Program Manager for Infrastructure Projects prepare the PPMP of infrastructure projects to be forwarded to the City Budget Officer for evaluation to ensure consistency with the Procuring Entity's budget proposal and compliance with existing budgeting rules and thereafter to the BAC Secretariat for consolidation and preparation of the indicative APP;

b.	BAC members adhere with the pertinent provisions of RA No. 9184 on the notification of all other bidders on the BAC recommendation; 

c.	City Accountant compute the liquidated damages in the delivery of uniforms, bags and harvester and demand payment of such from the supplier;

d.	City Engineer (i) stop the practice of renting construction equipment and tools for projects undertaken by administration; and (ii) comply with the requirements on the posting of the prescribed signboards at the project site; and

e.	City Accountant, Engineer, and General Services Officer submit the           lacking documents to the Audit Team for audit purposes.

We recommended that the:

a. City School Board (CSB) consolidate all requests for procurement, prepare and submit the PPMP for supplies and materials to the City BAC, consolidate into an APP, copy furnished the Audit Team; 

b. City Accountant and Budget Officer reconcile the recorded appropriations, allotments and obligations in their respective records; 

c. City Accountant submit the necessary documentary requirements for the procured goods; and

d. City Mayor require the City Supervisor of the City School to immediately submit the Liquidation Reports (LRs) for the expenses incurred for the financial assistance granted to them for recording in the books of accounts of the City.

