We recommended that the:
a. City Accountant (i) analyze the recorded Public Infrastructures; (ii) prepare the necessary JEV to record the 25% of the public infrastructures transferred in the registry; and (iii) prepare a subsidiary record for each component of the road network and Local Road Network Ledger Card; and (iv) exert extra effort to retrieve the data prior to CY 2002 to establish the correct date beginning balance of the Infrastructure Assets account;
b. GSO maintain Local Road Inventory, Road Map and Local Road Property Ledger Card;
c. Inventory Committee conduct physical count of the road network and prepare Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network (RPCLRN); and
d. City Engineer provide the City Accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended that the: 
a. City Disaster Risk Reduction Management Officer (CDRRMO) prepare and submit to the Audit Team the LDRRMF Investment Plan (LDRRMFIP) in accordance with the format provided in Annex A of COA Circular No. 2012-002 to reflect the allocation for Quick Respond Fund (QRF) in lump sum and disaster mitigation, prevention and preparedness with details as to projects and activities to be funded, as well as the list of projects and activities charged to the unexpended LDRRMF of previous years;
b. CDRRMO (i) ensure that all the proposed programs/projects for disaster be implemented during the year to give assurance on the readiness of the City in case of calamity; (ii) in case there is change in the previously proposed projects, see to it that  the Disaster Council  is guided by Department of Interior and Local Government (DILG), Department of Budget and Management (DBM) and National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council (NDRMMC) Joint Circular (JC) No. 2013-01 on the release and utilization of the unexpended balance of disaster fund for new expenditure items upon submission of a revised Annual Investment Plan (AIP) as approved by the local Sanggunian and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) upon recommendation the council and in accordance with the approved disaster plan; and (iii) prepare Supplemental AIP for the proposed projects  in the Supplemental Budget.
c. City Accountant, City Budget Officer (CBO) and the CDRRMO reconcile the balances appearing in the Registry of Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations (RAAO) and the Report on Utilization of DRRMF;
d. City Accountant draw JEV transferring from General Fund to Trust Fund the amount of ₱646,567.39 under QRF to reflect the correct balance of DRRM Trust Liability account; and
e. CBO and City Planning and Development Officer (i) strictly adhere with the regulations cited in Local Budget Operation Manual and the provision on the use of savings, appropriations, accounting for lawful expenditures and realignment of funds stated in Implementing Rulres and Regulations (IRR) of RA No. 7160; and (ii) see to it that thorough study and planning be conducted before realignment of funds to avoid adverse effect on the on-going programs of the City.

